text.section:
To investigate allegations of practices violating the provisions of this chapter, the commission may:
Issue subpoenas to compel attendance of witnesses and the production of books, papers, documents, or other evidence;
Administer oaths;
Review evidence;
Enter the office or branch office of any principal broker for the purpose of inspecting all documents required by the commission to be maintained in the principal broker's office or branch office which relate to the allegations of practices violating the provisions of this chapter;
Examine witnesses; and
Pay appropriate witness fees.
